rows.Review Evidence:
Verify that the regulations:
1) require AMOs to implement an SMS that is acceptable to the State;
2) require the SMS to be established in accordance with the SMS framework elements contained in Appendix 2 to Annex 19; and 
3) comply with the latest amendments to Annex 19.
Notes to the auditor: 
1) The SMS framework components and elements in Appendix 2 to Annex 19 are:
1. Safety policy and objectives:
    1.1 Management commitment; 
    1.2 Safety accountability and responsibilities; 
    1.3 Appointment of key safety personnel; 
    1.4 Coordination of emergency response planning; 
    1.5 SMS documentation; 
2. Safety risk management: 
    2.1 Hazard identification; 
    2.2 Safety risk assessment and mitigation; 
3. Safety assurance: 
    3.1 Safety performance measurement and monitoring;
    3.2 The management of change; 
    3.3 Continuous improvement of the SMS; 
4. Safety promotion: 
    4.1 Training and education; 
    4.2 Safety communication.
2) This PQ is only applicable to approved maintenance organizations (AMOs) providing services to operators of aeroplanes or helicopters engaged in international commercial air transport.

rows.İncelenecek Kanıtlar:
Düzenlemelerin aşağıdaki hususları sağladığını doğrulayın:
1) AMO'ların Devlet tarafından kabul edilebilir bir SMS uygulamasını zorunlu kılması;
2) SMS'nin, Annex 19 Ek 2'de yer alan SMS çerçevesi unsurlarına uygun olarak tesis edilmesini zorunlu kılması; ve
3) Annex 19'daki en son değişikliklere uygun olması.
Denetçiye notlar:
1) Annex 19 Ek 2'deki SMS çerçevesi bileşenleri ve unsurları şunlardır:
1. Emniyet politikası ve hedefleri:
    1.1 Yönetimin taahhüdü;
    1.2 Emniyet hesap verebilirliği ve sorumlulukları;
    1.3 Kilit emniyet personelinin atanması;
    1.4 Acil durum müdahale planlamasının koordinasyonu;
    1.5 SMS dokümantasyonu;
2. Emniyet riski yönetimi:
    2.1 Tehlike tanımlama;
    2.2 Emniyet riski değerlendirmesi ve hafifletilmesi;
3. Emniyet güvencesi:
    3.1 Emniyet performansının ölçülmesi ve izlenmesi;
    3.2 Değişiklik yönetimi;
    3.3 SMS'nin sürekli iyileştirilmesi;
4. Emniyetin teşviki:
    4.1 Eğitim ve öğretim;
    4.2 Emniyet iletişimi.
2) Bu PQ yalnızca, uluslararası ticari hava taşımacılığı yapan uçak veya helikopter işletmecilerine hizmet sağlayan onaylı bakım kuruluşları (AMO'lar) için geçerlidir.

rows.Review Evidence:
Verify that:
1) the State has identified competency requirements for personnel responsible for the acceptance and continuous surveillance of an SMS;
2) the content of the training programme addresses the SMS framework elements contained in Appendix 2 to Annex 19; 
3) the training also includes (but is not limited to) the following:
   a) evaluation and acceptance of an AMO’s SMS;
   b) evaluation and acceptance of an AMO’s safety performance indicators (SPIs); 
   c) continuous surveillance of the AMO’s SMS in a safety management environment;
   d) hazard identification and risk management processes and methodologies;
   e) protection of safety data, safety information and related sources; 
   f) enforcement under the framework of SMS; and
   g) soft skills (e.g. effective communication skills, negotiation skills, conflict resolution, etc.);
4) a training plan has been implemented;
5) initial, OJT and recurrent training, as applicable, with specified-time periods are included; and
6) training records are systematically retained.
Notes to the auditor:
1) The framework components and elements in Appendix 2 to Annex 19 are addresses in PQ 5.901.
2) This PQ is only applicable to approved maintenance organizations (AMOs) providing services to operators of aeroplanes or helicopters engaged in international commercial air transport.

rows.İncelenecek Kanıtlar:
